body.p: I'm from Latvia, born in 2004, currently live in the Netherlands. I had been learning programming since the age of 13. Throughout my life I have formed a solid foundation consisting of both hard and soft skills. Some of the non-specific technical hard skills:

li.p: Proficient in mathematics, mastered high school math and a bit of calculus and neural network theory. Have developed a logical and consequent reasoning, ready to take on new technical concepts when needed;
Have been using personal computer since the dawn of my life, mainly on Windows XP, Windows 10. During the last years, I have been using Linux - Ubuntu at the beginning, and then Arch Linux;

For the entire duration of my learning, I had been solving problems, one after another - this has really helped me develop my problem-solving skills and my stubbornness - when I simply stick to the problem until I resolve it or find another way to tacke it;
